Joint discussion on problems related to the writing of the Master's theses. Justification and analysis of the choices made in the course of the research process (theory, methods). Formalisation of the Master's thesis according to requirements.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course aims at supporting students in the course of writing their Master's theses and developing their academic writing skills.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student: 1) be familiar with modern research methods in social science and select them in accordance with research tasks; 2) recognise and analyse earlier and recent studies in their field of research, and synthesise the results obtained in identifying a new research problem; 3) present the results of the research and be able to defend their views in discussion.
